      "name": "fresh parsley",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, bring the beef broth to a boil over high heat.",
    "Add the lamb pieces to the pot and return to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped onion, carrot, and potato to the pot and continue to simmer for 20 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.",
    "Stir in the ketchup, salt, and black pepper, and continue to simmer for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the heat and let it cool slightly before serving.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and serve hot."
  ],
